PAD tips its hat
for Young
One hundred fifty years' service with Pan American World Airways is
the occasion for our celebration tonight - - a celebration to honor as
guests the six fellow employees whose pictures appear on this page.
Each of them has completed 25 years' service with the Company, thus
qualifying for the "Quarter Century Club, " the membership of which
is both distinctive and limited.
Twenty-five years is almost back to "the beginning of time" in terms
of the Company's life. It is the most progressive half of the history of
powered flight. During this period each of our Quarter Century members
has, in his own sphere, contributed in large measure to the Company's
growth and development, and to the progress of air transportation in
general.
It should be a source of considerable pride to each of them,
as it is to us, that they have had a part in numerous accomplishments
which are aviation history.
We now look forward to a continuing pleasant association with our
honored guests.
May the coming years be happy ones for them -
years in which their contributions will continue to redound to their
benefit, as well as to the further development of the World's Most
Experienced Airline.
Pan American World Airways
Pacific-Alaska Division

properties.sfomuseum:description: Event program produced by Pan American Airways System, Pacific-Alaska Division, for 25-year employee recognition, dated December 1, 1954; white cover with full color illustration of Strato Clipper in flight over clipper ship on water and blue text, “Yankee Clippers carry on”; interior contents: message from Clarence Young, menu, and photographic images of six 25-year employees: “Jack” Poindexter, “Hal” de Nourie, “Walt” Ziegler, Kathleen Hitchcock, Ralph Beecher, and “Lan” Turner.
